Dixons Group Plc said shareholders at aspecial meeting of Cyclops Corp approved the previouslyannounced merger of Cyclops with Dixons.    Under the terms of the merger, Dixons said the remainingpublic Cyclops shareholders are to receive 95 dlrs a share.    Dixons also said the previously announced sale of Cyclopssteel and nonresidential construction businesses to a former Alleghany Corp &lt;Y> subsidiary is expected to be completed June30. After the sale, Cyclops will retain its specialty retailingbusiness and change its name to Silo Inc, said Dixons. Reuter&#3;